# start Validation Reply Form
_vrf_PLAT790_jin28               
;
PROBLEM: Centre of Gravity not Within Unit Cell: Resd.  #          1 Note  
RESPONSE: This is an incorrect decision by cifcheck that will be corrected
soon by the program's author. 
;
_vrf_PLAT906_jin28               
;
PROBLEM: Large K value in the Analysis of Variance ......      2.812 Check 
RESPONSE: 
Usually data integration algorithms underestimate the background
 and produces slightly elevated values of Fo, resulting in higher Fo/Fc 
values. These are most pronounced for the weakest intensities.
;
_vrf_PLAT911_jin28               
;
PROBLEM: Missing # FCF Refl Between THmin & STh/L=  0.600          3 Report
RESPONSE: 
We believe that there is a good reason to use statistical analysis and 
if some reflections are outliers they harm rather than improve the 
refinement.  The statistical analysis was conducted with program 
G4_fcf_filter published on my web site 
http://xray.chem.wisc.edu/Resources.html. 
 It uses the approach described by Prince, E., Nicholson, W.L. 
(1983) Acta Cryst A39, 407-410. For the suggested value for the 
outlier cutoff see Rollett J.S. (1988) Crystallographic Computing 
4, 149-166, Oxford University Press.
;
# end Validation Reply Form
